@Chadimus The Doll is literally a doll inside the Hunter’s Dream that comes to life when the player has at least 1 insight (represents understanding of the eldritch truth, usually obtained from either the wisdom of madmen or seeing bosses). She serves as a caretaker for hunters who are capable of traveling to the dream either at will or when they die, channeling blood echos of enemies to level them up. She was made in the image of the horny old cripple Gehrman, host of the dream’s pupil Lady Maria because he was obsessed with her but she killed herself. There is almost certainly something more to the doll than just all that though, as she bleeds pale blood like many of the eldritch gods in the game and she’s capable of outliving both Gehrman and the god responsible for the dream, the Moon Presence.
